parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Intrusion in Rear Taillight Assembly (Racetrack Light)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water intrusion into the rear taillight assembly can cause the lights to malfunction or fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: Water accumulation in the taillight assembly
malfunctioning or failure of brake lights
marker lights
or license plate lights
electrical smell or burning smell
and difficulty passing safety inspections.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Intrusion in Rear Tail Light Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water intrusion into the rear tail light assembly can cause electrical shorts, corrosion, and failure of the lights, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Water accumulation in the tail light assembly
corrosion on electrical components
failure of brake lights
turn signals
and backup camera
flickering or dimming of lights
and complete loss of lighting function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of issues, including loss of lighting function, malfunctioning of climate control and infotainment systems, and failure of safety features like airbags.
symptoms: Intermittent or complete loss of lighting function
malfunctioning of climate control and infotainment systems
failure of airbags
and unexpected shutdown of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and shifter issues can cause difficulty shifting gears, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Difficulty shifting gears
clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and unexpected shifting into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission gears seize without warning
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the transmission jerks harshly when shifting gears
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission indicator light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shift selector can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into gear without warning
the vehicle moves forward when in park
the vehicle does not shift into reverse
the shift indicator light blinks or illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The auto start/stop feature can cause the vehicle to restart unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle restarts unexpectedly when coming to a stop
the vehicle moves forward when the driver thinks it is turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.
